{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is at a module boundary: manifest validation must gate module import/execution. A unit test of only `validateManifest` can pass while loader still imports plugin code too early. Rejected System because behavior text is about loader sequencing, not subprocess/network/OS-specific behavior. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI output is involved.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose `manifest.json` omits a required field and whose entry module has an observable side effect (e.g., writes a marker file or toggles shared state on import). Run the real loader pipeline (discover -> validate -> resolve -> load). Assert: loader reports validation rejection, marker side effect never occurs, and `onLoad` is never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when dependency resolver output is handed to lifecycle executor; single-function unit checks miss cross-module ordering bugs. Rejected System because no real network/subprocess/OS primitive is required; in-process plugins and local filesystem are sufficient. Rejected Agentic/Workflow due no model dependence.","test_description":"Set up two real plugin folders: A depends on B. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory/log file sequence. Run loader end-to-end for local plugins. Assert call order is `[B, A]` and both load successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Need resolver + load orchestrator interaction: detecting cycle is not enough; neither plugin may execute. A pure graph unit test can miss accidental partial loads. Rejected System since this is in-process dependency-graph behavior, not OS/network/subprocess. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because deterministic logic only.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies and observable import/`onLoad` side effects. Execute loader. Assert: cycle error/report includes A<->B relation, no `onLoad` calls for either plugin, and no entry-module side effects occurred.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is sequencing across importer and lifecycle dispatcher. Unit-testing hook invocation alone cannot catch wrong import-before-hook ordering. Rejected System: behavior does not require external process or network; Node import semantics can be exercised in-process with local files. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: no AI step.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` at import time, and whose `onLoad` asserts the flag is already true (or logs observed value). Run loader. Assert `onLoad` sees flag true and no ordering violation occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Requires dependency graph + error-isolation policy in orchestrator. Unit tests of try/catch logic miss dependency-aware continuation behavior across plugins. Rejected System because no real external infra is needed beyond local plugin modules. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior is deterministic and non-LLM.","test_description":"Create plugins: `core` (throws in `onLoad`), `independent` (no dependency on `core`), and `dependent` (depends on `core`). Run loader. Assert: `core` failure is reported; `independent` still loads and its `onLoad` runs; `dependent` does not load due to dependency failure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
